'''Frank Morris''' (born August 25, 1981 in [[Boise, Idaho]]) is an [[United States|American]] competitive [[speedcubing|speedcuber]].

He is best known as the 2005 World Champion for solving the Rubik's [[5x5x5]] cube.  He is also known for having held [[World Cube Association]] recognized world records for both the Rubik's 4x4x4 cube single solve time, as well as the Rubik's 5x5x5 cube single solve time and average time.  Frank is also featured on the [http://www.cubefreak.com/ Cubefreak] speed cuber trading cards.  Known aliases include "Frunk Murnis."

